This paper is about model-free reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a new exploration method for model-free RL, which falls under the category of exploration/exploitation trade-off in RL. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the efficiency and performance of the proposed method, which could fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of polynomial time algorithms, which could fall under the category of Mathematical Optimization (cs.MA).
